The paper discusses the development of interfaces and workflows for editing light field data, which is a subfield of computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The study also involves analyzing user performance and preferences, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of hidden Markov chain analysis, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
